{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JSXPgVZurxykw9YHveLX2y","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the evolution system. Let me compile a detailed report of all the findings.\n\n## Summary of Evolution System\n\nI've conducted a thorough search and read all the relevant files in the Cloche evolution system. Here's a comprehensive overview:\n\n### Core Components\n\n**1. Evolution System Architecture**\n- Located in `/workspace/internal/evolution/`\n- Multi-stage pipeline: Collector → Classifier → Reflector → Executor Branches (3 parallel) → Audit Logger\n- Triggered after every workflow completion with debouncing (default 30s)\n- Operates within daemon (cloched), not in CLI or container agents\n\n**2. The Curator (Prompt Evolution)**\nFile: `/workspace/internal/evolution/curator.go`\n\nThe Curator uses ACE (Agentic Context Engineering) principles to evolve prompts:\n- Takes a Lesson with `Target` (prompt file path), `Insight` (observation), and `SuggestedAction`\n- Reads the current prompt file\n- Sends to LLM with system prompt enforcing ACE rules:\n  - Append lessons as structured bullets in \"## Learned Rules\" section\n  - Deduplicate: if lesson refines existing rule, update in place rather than appending\n  - Preserve ALL existing content exactly\n  - Keep rules concise and actionable\n- LLM returns updated content (possibly wrapped in markdown code fences)\n- Calls `stripCodeFences()` to extract content between ` ``` ` markers, preserving only the updated prompt\n- Takes a snapshot before writing the file\n- Returns a `Change` record documenting the update\n\n**3. The Audit Logger (Evolution Tracking)**\nFile: `/workspace/internal/evolution/audit.go`\n\nThree core responsibilities:\n\na) **Snapshot System** - `Snapshot(relativePath string) (snapName string, error)`\n   - Creates `.cloche/evolution/snapshots/` directory\n   - Copies file before it's modified\n   - Names snapshots: `YYYYMMDDTHHMMSS-filename` format\n   - Used by both Curator and DSL Mutator to preserve pre-change state\n\nb) **JSONL Logging** - `Log(result *EvolutionResult) error`\n   - Appends to `.cloche/evolution/log.jsonl`\n   - One JSON object per line\n   - Records every evolution pass with ID, timestamp, classification, changes, and knowledge delta\n   - Enables full audit trail of all system changes\n\nc) **Knowledge Base Update** - `UpdateKnowledge(workflowName string, lessons []Lesson) error`\n   - Maintains `.cloche/evolution/knowledge/<workflow>.md`\n   - ACE-style structured document with itemized bullets\n   - Each lesson includes: ID, category, confidence level, insight, suggested action, evidence (run IDs)\n   - Creates with header on first run\n   - Appends new lessons with formatting\n\n**4. Data Types**\nFile: `/workspace/internal/evolution/types.go`\n\nCore structures:\n```go\n// Input to Classifier and Reflector\nCollectedData struct {\n    Runs            []*domain.Run\n    Captures        map[string][]*domain.StepExecution // run_id -> executions\n    KnowledgeBase   string                             // knowledge/<workflow>.md content\n    CurrentPrompts  map[string]string                  // relative path -> content\n    CurrentWorkflow string                             // .cloche file content\n    WorkflowPath    string                             // path to .cloche file\n    ProjectDir      string\n    WorkflowName    string\n}\n\n// Structured lesson extracted by Reflector\nLesson struct {\n    ID              string   // \"lesson-YYYYMMDD-NNN\"\n    Category        string   // \"prompt_improvement\" or \"new_step\"\n    StepType        string   // \"script\" or \"agent\" for new_step\n    Target          string   // relative prompt file path for prompt_improvement\n    Insight         string   // observation\n    SuggestedAction string   // concrete change\n    Evidence        []string // list of run IDs supporting the lesson\n    Confidence      string   // \"high\" (4+ occurrences), \"medium\" (2-3), \"low\" (1)\n}\n\n// Result of each evolution pass\nEvolutionResult struct {\n    ID             string   // \"evo-<nanoTimestamp>\"\n    ProjectDir     string\n    WorkflowName   string\n    TriggerRunID   string   // which run triggered this evolution\n    Timestamp      string   // RFC3339\n    Classification string   // \"bug\", \"feedback\", \"feature\", \"enhancement\", \"chore\"\n    Changes        []Change // what was modified\n    KnowledgeDelta string   // summary of knowledge updates\n}\n\n// Single file modification\nChange struct {\n    Type     string // \"prompt_update\", \"add_script\", \"add_step\"\n    File     string // relative path\n    Reason   string // the lesson insight\n    Snapshot string // snapshot filename (YYYYMMDDTHHMMSS-filename)\n}\n```\n\n### Pipeline Stages\n\n**Stage 1: Collector** (`collector.go`)\n- Gathers runs since last evolution pass\n- Reads knowledge base, workflow DSL, and all referenced prompt files\n- Extracts prompt file paths via regex on `file(\"...\")` patterns\n- Returns `CollectedData` for analysis\n\n**Stage 2: Classifier** (`classifier.go`)\n- LLM categorizes run prompt into: bug, feedback, feature, enhancement, chore\n- Defaults to \"feature\" on error/parse failure\n- Returns single classification string\n\n**Stage 3: Reflector** (`reflector.go`)\n- LLM analyzes execution traces and extracts structured lessons\n- Receives all collected data (runs, captures, knowledge base, prompts, workflow)\n- Returns JSON: `{\"lessons\": [...]}`\n- Filters by `MinConfidence` threshold before returning\n- Confidence levels: high=3, medium=2, low=1, default=0\n\n**Stage 4: Executor Branches** (three parallel paths based on lesson category)\n\na) **Prompt Curator** - `prompt_improvement` lessons\n   - Merges lesson into prompt file via LLM\n   - Deduplicates/updates existing rules\n   - Strips code fences from LLM response\n   - Snapshots before writing\n\nb) **Script Generator** (`scriptgen.go`) - `new_step` lessons with script type\n   - LLM generates shell script implementing the check\n   - Returns JSON: `{\"path\": \"scripts/<name>.sh\", \"content\": \"...\"}`\n   - Creates with executable permissions (0755)\n\nc) **DSL Mutator** - structural changes to workflow DSL\n   - Handled by `dsl.Mutator` in separate package\n   - Operations: AddStep, AddWiring, RewireResult, UpdateCollect\n   - Validates workflow after mutation\n\n**Stage 5: Audit Logger**\n- Takes snapshots of modified files\n- Logs evolution pass to JSONL\n- Updates knowledge base with lessons\n- Saves to SQLite evolution_log table if available\n\n### How Prompts Are Currently Written\n\nFiles involved:\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/curator.go` - main prompt writing logic\n- Curator.Apply() method writes updated prompts to disk via `os.WriteFile()`\n\nProcess:\n1. Read current prompt from disk\n2. Call Curator.Apply() with Lesson containing Target path\n3. Curator calls LLM with system prompt enforcing ACE rules and user prompt containing:\n   - `## Current Prompt Content\\n```\\n[current content]\\n```\\n\\n## Lesson to Merge\\nInsight: [insight]\\nSuggested Action: [suggested_action]`\n4. LLM returns updated content (may be wrapped in code fences)\n5. stripCodeFences() extracts content between ` ``` ` markers\n6. os.WriteFile() writes to disk with 0644 permissions\n7. Audit logger creates snapshot before write\n\n### Project Structure\n\nEvolution state lives in `.cloche/evolution/`:\n```\n.cloche/\n  evolution/\n    log.jsonl                          # append-only audit trail (JSONL format)\n    knowledge/\n      <workflow>.md                    # ACE-style knowledge base per workflow\n    snapshots/\n      <YYYYMMDDTHHMMSS>-<filename>    # pre-change file backups\n```\n\n### Configuration\n\nPer-project in `.cloche/config.toml`:\n```toml\n[evolution]\nenabled = true                # master switch\ndebounce_seconds = 30         # wait after last run before analyzing\nmin_confidence = \"medium\"     # minimum lesson confidence to act on\nmax_prompt_bullets = 50       # cap on knowledge bullets per prompt\n```\n\n### Key Files to Reference\n\n1. **Design Documents:**\n   - `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md` - full system design (449 lines)\n   - `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md` - implementation plan\n\n2. **Implementation:**\n   - `/workspace/internal/evolution/curator.go` - Curator with ACE-style prompt curation\n   - `/workspace/internal/evolution/audit.go` - AuditLogger with snapshots and JSONL logging\n   - `/workspace/internal/evolution/types.go` - data structures\n   - `/workspace/internal/evolution/orchestrator.go` - pipeline wiring\n   - `/workspace/internal/evolution/reflector.go` - lesson extraction\n   - `/workspace/internal/evolution/collector.go` - data gathering\n   - `/workspace/internal/evolution/classifier.go` - run classification\n   - `/workspace/internal/evolution/scriptgen.go` - script generation\n   - `/workspace/internal/evolution/trigger.go` - debounce triggering\n   - `/workspace/internal/evolution/llmclient.go` - command-based LLM invocation\n   - `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run struct with ProjectDir field\n\n3. **Tests:**\n   - `/workspace/internal/evolution/evolution_test.go` - comprehensive unit tests\n   - `/workspace/test/integration/evolution_test.go` - integration tests\n\n### Key Insights\n\n1. **ACE-Style Prompt Evolution**: The Curator treats prompts as structured playbooks that accumulate lessons as bullets, not monolithic documents that get rewritten\n\n2. **Code Fence Stripping**: LLM responses are cleaned to extract only content between ` ``` ` markers, preventing commentary from leaking into prompt files\n\n3. **Snapshot Strategy**: Pre-change snapshots are created for all modified files, enabling auditing and potential future reversions\n\n4. **Multi-Project Scoping**: All evolution state is scoped by `project_dir + workflow_name`, enabling daemon to manage multiple concurrent projects\n\n5. **Debounced Triggering**: Rapid successive runs are batched together (30s default debounce) to avoid wasting analysis on incomplete workflows\n\n6. **Confidence Filtering**: Only lessons meeting minimum confidence threshold proceed to executor branches"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aed3bd8041c2027ed (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 53838\ntool_uses: 21\nduration_ms: 39781</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e4cfca95-080f-4ed6-8c8d-4b515387a6e7","uuid":"cc6be8eb-5b54-46aa-b0df-00b6901812e0","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the evolution system, specifically the Curator, Audit, and how prompt files are written. Find and read:\n1. Any files related to \"curator\" or \"Curator\" \n2. Any files related to \"audit\" in the evolution context\n3. Any files related to evolution results/changes\n4. Look for how snapshots work\n\nSearch in the entire repo. Be very thorough - read the full content of all relevant files.","agentId":"aed3bd8041c2027ed","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the evolution system. Let me compile a detailed report of all the findings.\n\n## Summary of Evolution System\n\nI've conducted a thorough search and read all the relevant files in the Cloche evolution system. Here's a comprehensive overview:\n\n### Core Components\n\n**1. Evolution System Architecture**\n- Located in `/workspace/internal/evolution/`\n- Multi-stage pipeline: Collector → Classifier → Reflector → Executor Branches (3 parallel) → Audit Logger\n- Triggered after every workflow completion with debouncing (default 30s)\n- Operates within daemon (cloched), not in CLI or container agents\n\n**2. The Curator (Prompt Evolution)**\nFile: `/workspace/internal/evolution/curator.go`\n\nThe Curator uses ACE (Agentic Context Engineerin